Open "Server Manager" and click on "Add roles and features."
Select "Network Policy and Access Services" and follow the wizard to install the role.
After installing the role, open "Network Policy Server" from the Tools menu.
Import NPS configuration by right-clicking on the server name in the left pane, selecting "Import Configuration," and choosing the XML file.
After configuring Network Policy Server (NPS), you can define network access policies for authentication, authorization, and accounting of network clients, enhancing the security and control of your network environment.




